Within about a minute of both nodes reaching RUNNING, open the **master** above
and go to Config -> System -> Redundancy. You should see **PEER CONNECTED: Yes**
and **Sync Status: Good**; the backup pulls a one-time full config sync from the
master. No mode selection or certificate approval is needed - the seeded
`redundancy.xml` set the roles and the plain link auto-approves.

If the pair has not formed, confirm both containers are up and re-check after the
backup finishes its first sync. The full manual pairing runbook (and the SSL
variant) lives in `docs/docs/guides/redundancy.md`.

> **Security:** this stack uses a **plain, non-SSL** redundancy link with an
> `Unrestricted` Gateway Network policy. That is safe only on an isolated demo
> network - redundancy replicates the entire gateway (projects, tags, secrets)
> over the link. For any cross-host or production deployment, switch to SSL on
> port 8060 with approved certificates.
